        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 20,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cost-effective industrial cleaning; picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) for ultra-minimal HAZ but less common for rubber. 20 ns balances ablation of contaminants with low heat input. Source: Laser physics in Applied Surface Science (2019) on polymer cleaning thresholds; ns pulses avoid melting unlike longer durations."
